The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 9: Tea production in June fell by three per cent to 105.44 million kg because of unsuitable weather conditions, according to latest Tea Board data. The production stood at 108.29 million kg in the same month last year. However, exports have surged to 13.74 million kg against 11.97 million kg in the year-ago period.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 9: National Pharmaceutical Pricing Authority (NPPA) has revised the prices of over 188 formulation packs, which include some of the popular pain relievers such as paracetamol and anti-inflamatory medicine ibuprofen.                            
	 Mumbai, Aug. 8: Sebi will hold its board meeting on August 13. While the agenda of the meeting has not been disclosed, sources said the board was expected to review the rules regarding the issuance of participatory notes by foreign investors.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 9: The finance ministry has said that the government proposed to involve state-run agencies and consumer federations in containing price rise by augmenting supplies in the market. It cautioned that tax cuts announced earlier might put pressure on the exchequer leading to inflationary tendencies.                            
	 Calcutta, Aug. 9: Allahabad Bank has raised its benchmark prime lending rate by 50 basis points to 14 per cent with effect from today. The hike will not be applicable to new housing loans up to Rs 30 lakh and all existing housing, personal, educational and auto loans.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 9: ONGC Videsh Ltd (OVL) Essar, Oil India Ltd (OIL) and Lakshmi N. Mittals investment firm have been shortlisted by Algeria to bid for oil blocks in its latest licen sing round. While OVL and OIL have been shortlisted as operators of oilfields, Mittal Investment Sarl and Essar have qualified to participate as financial investors.                            
	 Chandigarh, Aug. 8: Bharti Wal-Mart would commence its wholesale cash-and-carry operations by early next year from the northern region.                                                                                                                         
